  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the record for the heaviest weight ever lifted by a human being is claimed to be 6,270 pounds (2,840 kg), achieved by Paul Anderson in a backlift in 1957. However, various weightlifting and strength records exist across different categories and styles, such as clean and jerk, deadlift, and squat.\n\nAdditionally, in the world of powerlifting, Hafthor Bjornsson set a deadlift record of 1,104 pounds (501 kg) in 2020. It's important to note that these records can be subject to change as new feats of strength are attempted and validated. Always refer to the latest verified records for the most accurate information.",
